	<p>
	  Kim-san is Korean. He's a computer programmer for Hitachi.
	  We make very long conversations. The problem is that,
	  usually, Kim-san talks in Japanese with Hugo who then translates for me,
	  and it seems that going from Japanese to French/English there's a very 
	  high compression ratio: minutes of conversation are condensed
	  in a single sentence by Hugo. Lost in translation? it actually happens.
	 </p>
	 
